The following files feature were newly introduced in this update cycle is 
Disapproval of User

Model Helper Methods

User Model (Modules/Users/Models/User.php): Added a new helper method isDisapproved(): bool to easily check if a user's current status is disapproved without querying the database manually.
Status Model (Modules/Questions/Models/Status.php): Added a similar isDisapproved(): bool method to verify if a status object corresponds to the disapproved state.
API Routes (routes/api.php)
Added dedicated endpoints for Dean administrators to reject user applications:

PATCH /users/{userID}/disapprove: Route for disapproving a single user.
POST /users/disapprove-multiple: Route for bulk disapproving multiple users at once.
Database Constraints
Migrations (Modules/Users/Database/Migrations/2025_05_31_213032_add_status_id_to_users_table.php): Officially mapped the status_id of 3 to 'disapproved', integrating it directly into the application's core status list alongside 'pending' and 'registered'.
Seeders (Modules/Questions/Database/Seeders/StatusSeeder.php): Added 'disapproved' to the list of seeded statuses.
🔄 2. What Was Changed (Modified Files)
User Controller (

Modules/Users/Controllers/UserController.php
)
Major modifications were made to handle the actual disapproval process and side-effects:


disapproveUser(Request $request, $userID)
:

Authorization Check: Ensured only the Dean (via 

authorizeDeanAccess()
) can trigger a disapproval.
User Lookup: Finds the target user by their $userID using User::findOrFail($userID).
Status Update logic: Uses the newly refactored 

updateUserStatus($user, 'disapproved', false)
 to simultaneously change the user status_id to the ID for 'disapproved' and update their isActive flag to false.
State Refresh: Refreshes the user model state with $user->refresh() after the update is processed.

disapproveMultipleUsers(Request $request)
:

Authorization Check: Similar to single disapproval, strictly limits this action to Deans.
Data Validation: Ensures the $request->userIDs array exists and is formatted correctly.
Bulk Processing: Iterates through the provided list of IDs (foreach ($userIDs as $id)), loads the user (User::find($id)), and if valid, updates their status using 

updateUserStatus($user, 'disapproved', false)
.
Private Helper Method 

updateUserStatus($user, $status, $isActive)
:

Was utilized or explicitly defined to look up the correct status_id from the statuses table (e.g., matching 'disapproved') and update both status_id and isActive atomically using $user->update(...).